"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-news-from-amelie-to-the-olympics-nils-politt-uses-famous-paris-cafe-during-mens-road-race-for-emergency-toilet-break\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  German rider finishes 70th after unplanned mid-race pitstop  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9938698085701202, \"rank\": 0.005031773294078592, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  Clients in the famous Caf\\u00e9 des 2 Moulins in central Paris on Saturday had a closer encounter with one member of theOlympic Games Men's Road Racepeloton than they might have realistically expected when participantNils Politttook an emergency mid-race toilet break in the establishment's facilities.\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 356, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caf\\u00e9_des_2_Moulins\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caf\\u00e9 des 2 Moulins\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q11707\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caf\\u00e9_des_2_Moulins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caf\\u00e9_des_2_Moulins\"}, {\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.611287977987147e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suffering from stomach issues, as the German rider later told reporters, Politt dived into the caf\\u00e9 in the closing kilometres of the race, won by Belgium'sRemco Evenepoel.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9938698085701202, \"rank\": 0.005031773294078592, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The caf\\u00e9 became a tourist destination after it featured in several scenes in the 2001 cult movieAm\\u00e9lie.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Politt, though, had other priorities than sightseeing on his mind when he quickly entered the caf\\u00e9 on Paris' \\u00a0Rue Lepic at the bottom of the Butte Montmartre ascent on Saturday afternoon, weaving his way through a large number of customers in search of a lavatory.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.611287977987147e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rue Lepic\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\"}, {\"begin\": 1058, \"end\": 1068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4020518793172814e-14, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His emergency mission successfully accomplished, and cheered on by the clients and the massive crowds as he subsequently exited the caf\\u00e9, Politt then jumped back over the barriers, remounted his bike and continued racing.\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He completed the course, finishing nearly 20 minutes down on Evenepoel.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not count how much time it took me,\\\" Politt later told reporters.\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was really warm, we were drinking a lot of water, ate a lot of gels and normally I do not have problems.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today I had an upset stomach.\\\"\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nils Politt e il bisogno fisiologico espletato presso il Caf\\u00e9 des 2 Moulins \\ud83d\\ude4c pic.twitter.com/kbqQIuzudNAugust 3, 2024  Get unlimited access to all of our coverage of the 2024 Olympic Games - including breaking news and analysis reported by our journalists on the ground from every event across road, mountain bike, track and BMX racing as it happens and more.Find out more.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1852, \"end\": 1870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caf\\u00e9_des_2_Moulins\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caf\\u00e9 des 2 Moulins\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q11707\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caf\\u00e9_des_2_Moulins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caf\\u00e9_des_2_Moulins\"}, {\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX_racing\", \"score\": 0.9992382870941527, \"rank\": 0.000762293554701649, \"text\": \"BMX racing\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX_racing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX_racing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alasdair Fotheringham has been reporting on cycling since 1991.\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2172, \"end\": 2193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alasdair_Fotheringham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alasdair Fotheringham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q1930187\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alasdair_Fotheringham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alasdair_Fotheringham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has covered every Tour de France since 1992 bar one, as well as numerous other bike races of all shapes and sizes, ranging from the Olympic Games in 2008 to the now sadly defunct Subida a Urkiola hill climb in Spain.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3172585648925232e-16, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9999916728139591, \"rank\": 8.257608263658968e-06, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as working forCyclingnews, he has also written forThe Independent,The Guardian,ProCycling,The ExpressandReuters.\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999898518581, \"rank\": 1.014815967488764e-08, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independen